const title = "Commercial Pressure Fryer Repair Los Angeles — Same Day";
const description = "Pressure fryer repair across SoCal. Henny Penny PFE-500/PFE-561, BKI LPF. Specialty chicken and fried-food pressure fryers. $120 diagnostic. (424) 325-0520.";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "How are pressure fryers different from open-pot or tube-fired fryers?",
    a: "Pressure fryers fry food in a sealed chamber under pressure (typically 12 to 14 PSI), which significantly reduces cooking time and produces a distinctive texture (the KFC-style fried chicken signature). The architecture adds three safety-critical components on top of standard fryer mechanics: pressure relief valve (must release excess pressure if it builds beyond safe range), pressure-rated lid gasket (must maintain seal under pressure for the cook cycle), and door interlock system (must prevent lid opening while chamber is pressurized). Service requires understanding pressure-vessel safety in addition to standard fryer mechanics."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you service Henny Penny PFE-500 and PFE-561?",
    a: "Yes. Henny Penny dominates the US pressure fryer market and the PFE-500 (smaller capacity) and PFE-561 (larger capacity) are the most-installed models in our service mix. We carry common Henny Penny pressure fryer parts on the van including pressure-rated lid gaskets, pressure relief valves, door interlock components. Henny Penny parts have excellent availability through their independent service network."
  },
  {
    q: "How often should pressure fryer safety components be inspected?",
    a: "Annually at minimum. Pressure relief valves should be tested for proper release pressure once per year. Lid gaskets should be inspected for compression set and replaced when they no longer maintain seal. Door interlock systems should be tested to confirm they prevent lid opening during pressurized cooking. We perform safety inspections as part of preventive maintenance visits and document results for your records. Failed pressure relief valve plus heating system overshoot equals a serious safety incident risk; this is one of the few service categories where we strongly recommend not deferring annual inspection."
  },
  {
    q: "My pressure fryer's lid gasket is leaking. Can I use any food-grade silicone gasket?",
    a: "No. Pressure fryer lid gaskets are pressure-rated, designed to maintain seal at 12 to 14 PSI cooking pressure across thousands of cycles. Standard food-grade silicone or general fryer gaskets aren't rated for repeated pressure cycling and will fail prematurely or, worse, fail catastrophically during a cook cycle. We use OEM Henny Penny or BKI pressure-rated gaskets exclusively. The aftermarket appliance parts industry has tried to substitute lower-cost gaskets here; on a pressure vessel that's a safety problem, not a cost-saving opportunity."
  },
  {
    q: "My door interlock won't release. Is the unit broken?",
    a: "Probably not broken. Door interlocks are designed to prevent lid opening while pressure remains in the chamber, so a 'won't release' interlock often means residual pressure hasn't fully vented. First step: confirm pressure has fully released through the steam vent solenoid valve. If the gauge reads zero and the interlock still won't release, the interlock mechanism itself or the pressure sensor signaling the interlock has failed. Either way, do not force the lid. We diagnose and repair the interlock circuit."
  },
  {
    q: "What's the typical service life of a Henny Penny pressure fryer?",
    a: "15 to 20 years on Henny Penny PFE series with regular safety inspections and maintenance. The pressure vessel itself has indefinite life if maintained. The wear items are lid gaskets (replace at 2 to 4 years), pressure relief valves (test annually, replace at 7 to 10 years), heating elements or igniters (year 8 to 12), filter pump motors (year 6 to 9), door interlock components (year 8 to 12). The economics favor repair through year 18+ because replacement units run $15,000 to $25,000+ for premium Henny Penny PFE configurations."
  },
  {
    q: "What's your warranty on pressure fryer repairs?",
    a: "Ninety days SDAR labor and parts warranty on the work we perform. Henny Penny and BKI manufacturer warranties processed separately when applicable, including their pressure vessel structural warranties. BHGS #A49573 and BBB Accredited Business. EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410."
  }
];

