<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Pressure fryer specialty service</p>
    <h2>Pressure-vessel cooking. Safety-critical. Henny Penny dominant.</h2>

    <p>Pressure fryers fry food in a sealed chamber under pressure (typically 12 to 14 PSI), reducing cooking time significantly and producing the distinctive texture that defines KFC-style fried chicken and high-end fried-food restaurants. The architecture adds three safety-critical components on top of standard fryer mechanics: pressure relief valve, pressure-rated lid gasket, door interlock system. Pressure fryer service requires pressure-vessel safety understanding in addition to standard fryer mechanics, and OEM-only parts on the safety components.</p>

    <p>We service pressure fryers across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside. The market: <strong>Henny Penny PFE series</strong> dominates the US pressure fryer market by a wide margin. PFE-500 (smaller capacity, common in smaller chicken specialty restaurants) and PFE-561 (larger capacity, common in chain operations) are the most-installed models. <strong>BKI LPF series</strong> (Standex International) is the secondary brand. <strong>Winston</strong> has pressure-related cooking products, though their primary market is CVap holding.</p>

    <p>$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. BHGS #A49573. EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410. BBB Accredited. Phones answered 24/7. Safety inspection documentation included on every preventive maintenance visit.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 FAILURE TREE -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Failure tree</p>
    <h2>Common pressure fryer failures and safety-critical components.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Seven failure modes cover the bulk of pressure fryer service calls. The first three are safety-critical and have specific OEM-only requirements. Aftermarket parts substitution on these components is not appropriate and not something we do.</p>

    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Lid gasket compression (year 2 to 4).</strong> Pressure-rated gasket designed to maintain seal at 12 to 14 PSI across thousands of cycles. Eventually compresses to the point where seal fails. Replacement requires OEM Henny Penny or BKI pressure-rated gasket only.</li>
      <li><strong>Pressure relief valve calibration drift / failure (year 7 to 10).</strong> Safety-critical. Should be tested annually to confirm proper release pressure. Replacement when calibration cannot be verified.</li>
      <li><strong>Door interlock safety system.</strong> Year 8 to 12 typical replacement. Interlock prevents lid opening during pressurized cooking. Must function correctly or unit is unsafe to operate.</li>
      <li><strong>Steam venting solenoid valve.</strong> Releases steam pressure at end of cook cycle. When fails, pressure remains in chamber and door interlock won't release.</li>
      <li><strong>Pressure gauge calibration drift.</strong> Operators rely on the gauge to verify pressure during cooking. Calibration check at safety inspection.</li>
      <li><strong>Heating element or igniter.</strong> Same as standard fryer. Electric models use heating element; gas models use igniter and burner.</li>
      <li><strong>Integrated filter pump.</strong> Henny Penny PFE includes integrated filter pump. Year 6 to 9 typical pump motor wear.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 REAL REPAIR STORIES -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Real repairs</p>
    <h2>Composite stories from the route.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Four pressure fryer jobs from the past 90 days. Models, symptoms, diagnosis, parts, time, total. Names omitted; the technical scenarios are typical.</p>

    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Chicken restaurant, Hollywood. Henny Penny PFE-500, 6 years old.</h3>
        <p>Lid gasket leaking during cook cycle, plus pressure relief valve hadn't been tested in over 4 years. Replaced lid gasket with OEM Henny Penny pressure-rated gasket, tested pressure relief valve (failed calibration test, replaced). Documented full safety inspection for owner records. Total: $120 plus $580 gasket plus $260 relief valve plus $140 labor = $1,100.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Specialty fried food restaurant, Pasadena. Henny Penny PFE-561, 9 years old.</h3>
        <p>Door interlock won't release after cook cycle. Diagnosed: residual pressure not venting due to steam venting solenoid valve sticky operation, plus pressure gauge drift indicated by inconsistent readings. Solenoid valve serviced (cleaned and rebuilt, didn't need replacement on this generation), pressure gauge replaced for accuracy on safety-critical readings. Total: $120 plus $290 gauge plus $140 solenoid service plus $340 labor = $890.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Caterer, Beverly Hills. BKI LPF, 7 years old.</h3>
        <p>Steam venting solenoid stuck open (pressure couldn't build to spec) plus filter pump motor noisy (year 7 wear). Replaced solenoid valve plus filter pump motor as one visit. Total: $120 plus $385 parts plus $215 labor = $720.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Asian restaurant chain, West LA. Henny Penny PFE-500, 11 years old.</h3>
        <p>Heating element open-circuit (no heat) plus thermocouple weakening. Replaced heating element with Henny Penny OEM, replaced thermocouple. Performed safety inspection while access was open: pressure relief valve tested fine, lid gasket showed early compression set (recommended replacement at next visit, year 11 is at the edge of gasket life). Total: $120 plus $620 parts plus $240 labor = $980.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 SCOPE -->
<section class="section section-gray">
